                width="560"
                height="349"
                src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/O5FBJyqfoLM?feature=oembed&start&end&wmode=opaque&loop=0&controls=1&mute=0&rel=1&modestbranding=0"
                allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
                allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </VideoFrame>
            <p class="mt-4">
              This short summary provides a comprehensive look at how redlining
              brought about housing segregation. Redlining is not limited to
              just housing - it can affect any place of identity, such as
              educational institutions, businesses, the community at large.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h5>How Redlining Shaped Black America As We Know It</h5>
            <VideoFrame>
              <iframe
                class="video-iframe"
                width="560"
                height="349"
                src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/2o-yD0wGxAc?feature=oembed&start&end&wmode=opaque&loop=0&controls=1&mute=0&rel=1&modestbranding=0"
                allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
                allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </VideoFrame>
            <p class="mt-4">
              This video demonstrates how redlining creates a vicious cycle of
              racism that spans generations. The book <em
                ><Link
                  href="https://www.amazon.com/Reproducing-Racism-Everyday-Choices-Advantage/dp/0814777120"
                  >Reproducing Racism: How Everyday Choices Lock In White
                  Advantages</Link
                >
              </em>, by Doria Rothmayr, sums up how redlining perpetuates
              racism.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div slot="third-col">
            <h5>
              Segregated by Design - Uncovering the Forgotten History of How Our
              Gorvernment Segregated America
            </h5>
            <VideoFrame>
